<Issue id="46264" key="FAB-18304" number="18304" project="10002" reporter="btl5037" assignee="manish-sethi" creator="btl5037" type="10004" summary="Full disks causes LevelDB corruption" priority="1" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2020-10-30 01:44:45.0" updated="2021-03-12 03:01:29.0" resolutiondate="2021-03-05 18:05:17.0" votes="0" watches="3" workflowId="60178" archived="N"> <description><! CDATA When the peer's disk, or the persistent volume mounted at the levelDB directory become full, the peer panics killing the process, including the current DB write in flight. When the peer restarts it cannot finish the startup sequence as a partial levelDB write occurred and it cant read the levelDB manifests.  Of note, this was on file storage, which is NFS-backed storage, which we know does not play well with databases.  This is likely related to: https://github.com/syndtr/goleveldb/issues/335  I will decorate this Jira with logs and more information shortly.  ></description> </Issue>
